The paper deals with a problem related to ordering and embedding of graphs, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The use of PQ-trees and their applications in constrained embedding problems suggest that the paper may also belong to the data structures and algorithms category (cs.DS).
